<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12154b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12154b">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12154b"> 154(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> 9<sup>th</sup> canon / no medius locus / for children</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Some codices contain a ninth canon &hellip; Children dying without baptism do not go to a &ldquo;middle place&rdquo; (<i>medius locus</i>), since the non-reception of baptism excludes both from &ldquo;the kingdom of heaven&rdquo; and from &ldquo;eternal life&rdquo;. <small> <a name="CEPEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPEL"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Pelagius&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) 607a</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12159h" href="c12all.htm#c12159h">VI.C.12:159(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
